Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.94,0:00:06.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What I mean is: four, five or six.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.06,0:00:10.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've had six cases this month. Count 'em, six. Kudo, what about you?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.49,0:00:13.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, me?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.40,0:00:15.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've solved seven cases.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.16,0:00:17.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dang, I lose again!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.99,0:00:21.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But say, Kudo, doesn't it seem that an awful lot of cases occur around you?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.08,0:00:25.83,Signs,,0,0,0,,Translator's Note: The {\i1}ji{\i0} character in Heiji's name means {\i1}next{\i0} or {\i1}follows{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.08,0:00:25.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, if your resigned to defeat, then the way you write your name suits you.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.17,0:00:29.00,Signs,,0,0,0,,Translator's Note: The {\i1}ichi{\i0} character in Shin'ichi's name means {\i1}one{\i0} or {\i1}best{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.17,0:00:29.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm Shin'ichi; therefore, I'm number one.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.09,0:00:32.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Idiot, you're number two.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.17,0:00:33.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eh? Number two?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.76,0:00:36.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it happened a while ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.39,0:00:39.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There was someone whose brain was sharper than yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.72,0:00:42.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.44,0:00:52.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Middle school detectives Heiji & Shin'ichi fight a deduction battle on the ski slope!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.86,0:00:54.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Will they solve the lift riding mystery?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.36,0:00:55.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perceiving the one and only truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.82,0:00:57.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With the body of a child and the brain of an adult.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.45,0:00:59.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His name is: Detective Conan!
Comment: 0,0:02:38.84,0:02:48.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This Meitantei Conan special is brought to you by P&G and by these sponsors.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.34,0:02:45.97,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,HATTORI HEIJI vs KUDO SHIN'ICHI\NDEDUCTION SHOWDOWN ON THE SKI SLOPE
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.31,0:02:54.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kazuha, say, are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.82,0:02:58.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If your leg's sprained badly, shouldn't you go back to the hotel?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.03,0:03:01.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's fine, I said. Fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.99,0:03:07.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Being alone at the hotel would be boring. It'll be more fun to be where I can watch everyone skiing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.45,0:03:08.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And also...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.12,0:03:11.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, sorry, sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.88,0:03:17.30,Signs,,0,0,0,,Translator's Note: Jizou statue - Statue of the popular Buddhist deity Jizou (a bodhisattva who guards children). A common sight throughout Japan.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.88,0:03:17.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So what I thought was a homely Jizou statue sitting in the snow is really a person?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.84,0:03:20.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What the heck's wrong with you? This is the fifth time!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.84,0:03:22.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Apologize to Kazuha now!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.55,0:03:24.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why should I have to apologize?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.51,0:03:28.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm just tossing snow on her sprain so it'll cool down and heal faster.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.52,0:03:34.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Teacher! Hattori{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} is flirting with some girls again!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.94,0:03:36.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What'd you guys say?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.40,0:03:37.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's got nothing to do with us!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.28,0:03:39.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The old ladies are getting angry!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.07,0:03:41.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Old ladies?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.03,0:03:43.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H-Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.11,0:03:43.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kazuha.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.12,0:03:48.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Give it up and hurry back to the hotel; you'll catch a cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.70,0:03:50.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Y-Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.83,0:03:52.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why are boys like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.67,0:03:58.21,Signs,,0,0,0,,Translator's Note: Yuki-onna (Snow Woman) - A youkai (spirit) popular in Japanese folk tales who appears as a beautiful woman on snowy nights and lures travelers to their deaths.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.67,0:03:56.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I hope the Yuki-onna of this mountain eats you for dinner!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.92,0:03:58.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Y-Yuki-onna?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.42,0:04:02.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The teacher told us a folklore story about these mountains called {\i1}The Legend of the Yuki-onna's Silver Gown{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.26,0:04:09.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A long time ago on this very mountain, there was an extraordinarily beautiful woman who wore a silver gown that sparkled with white light
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.85,0:04:15.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She caught sight of a good man traveling by foot on the mountain and she began to beguile him with a voice like the song of a snowstorm.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.15,0:04:21.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Will you exchange your most treasured possession for my silver gown?" she said.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.44,0:04:27.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The foolish man was overcome with lust by the sight of the white skin beneath the gown, and so he agreed to the condition.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.70,0:04:28.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A-And then?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.74,0:04:32.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,While the man was bundling the delicate gown in a wrapping cloth, he said:
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.29,0:04:37.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My only really treasured possession is this gun, but do you really want it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.42,0:04:40.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the woman responded from behind him:
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.92,0:04:41.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's not it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.42,0:04:43.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that case, do you want money?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.88,0:04:45.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's not it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.38,0:04:46.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My hat?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.72,0:04:47.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's not it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.89,0:04:55.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, without making a sound, the woman embraced him from behind with her naked body and:
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.39,0:04:57.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not cold things like those.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.44,0:05:03.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What I desperately want are the warm, warm...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.57,0:05:05.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...drops of blood...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.65,0:05:08.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...from your heart!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.87,0:05:09.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She cried.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.16,0:05:16.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Later, when they found the man's body, inside the wrapping cloth, instead of the silver gown,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.58,0:05:19.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,it was said they only found a large quantity of snow.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.42,0:05:23.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They say whenever there's a blizzard on this mountain, another victim appears.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.59,0:05:27.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems there was a new, awfully similar incident here four years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.01,0:05:32.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey! Kaihou Academy Middle School students! Lunch!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.31,0:05:35.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's already past two o'clock.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.06,0:05:37.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eh? Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.52,0:05:39.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No wonder I was hungry.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.56,0:05:42.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It looks like some other school is staying at this hotel too.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.36,0:05:46.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So it seems they shifted the time so we wouldn't get mixed-up in the cafeteria.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.24,0:05:54.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, isn't that Minowa Shouhei, the actor?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.08,0:05:56.12,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Minowa Shouhei (32)\NActor
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.58,0:05:56.08,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,What's he doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.29,0:06:02.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh yeah! I heard on TV they were making a movie based on an incident that really happened up on the snowy mountain.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.92,0:06:07.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? I heard it was a mystery movie about the Yuki-onna.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.26,0:06:08.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Heh, whatever.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.13,0:06:12.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, in any case, since that Minowa Shouhei guy is the lead,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.01,0:06:17.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,no matter which mysterious incident they're going for, I think he'll play the role of detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.35,0:06:20.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Detective eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.15,0:06:26.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Excuse me, I heard you'll be filming the third and concluding episode in the Yuki-onna series this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.40,0:06:30.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But didn't they say it would be a motif about an actual incident?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.12,0:06:32.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's correct too.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.08,0:06:35.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The deceased was my friend and our stuntman.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.33,0:06:38.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was there where it happened, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.62,0:06:39.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Excuse me, Minowa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.58,0:06:44.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The fact that the deceased was our Mizugami Jirou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} is kind of a secret.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.55,0:06:46.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.96,0:06:49.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,People on the Internet already know we're filming something about our late friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.93,0:06:54.47,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Ooyama Morizou (56)\NMovie Director
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.93,0:06:54.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, now. This film is being made in memory of his death.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.43,0:06:56.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, it's OK, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.47,0:06:59.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Someone who's dead and gone isn't going to come back and do handstands about it
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.02,0:07:03.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If we say our last movie is being devoted to Mizugami Jirou,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.48,0:07:06.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,it might bring out the sympathy of the audience.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.98,0:07:08.24,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Mimata Kousuke (27)\NStuntman
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.23,0:07:08.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That way the movie will be a hit or even our best.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.82,0:07:12.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We should be grateful to Mizugami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-senpai{\r}; he might make this movie a success.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.49,0:07:16.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And so should you, after all it was due to his death that you got the job as his replacement.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.50,0:07:20.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, shouldn't you be more careful?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.96,0:07:24.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After all, you're the one who has to take on the deceased Mizugami's stuntman role.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.50,0:07:27.50,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Tateishi Shizuku (31)\NMake-Up Specialist
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.34,0:07:27.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't be lured by the Yuki-onna, OK?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.88,0:07:28.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.13,0:07:31.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, I still don't really understand...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.55,0:07:35.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why would Mizugami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} go and leave a fiancée like you?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.22,0:07:37.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To have ended his own life...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.26,0:07:38.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who knows.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.22,0:07:41.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It wasn't suicide; it was murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.52,0:07:45.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And I figure one of you was the murderer.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.07,0:07:49.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's that police detective again.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.40,0:07:52.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, he's not a police detective anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.74,0:07:57.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was canned for putting too much time into the incident on this mountain, which was in the wrong prefecture.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.74,0:08:00.54,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Katashina Rikuto (35)\NPrivate Detective
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.24,0:08:00.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now I run a simple private detective business.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.87,0:08:03.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But still, no matter how you look at it, he committed suicide!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.08,0:08:05.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It does look that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.63,0:08:13.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Four years ago, a man riding alone on the lift at this ski joint, had a bullet shot through his head by a pistol and stopped drawing breath.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.18,0:08:17.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There was a gun in his right hand, gunpowder residue on his cuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.31,0:08:21.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Considering it normally, it looked like he offed himself with the pistol, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.39,0:08:23.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was a trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.60,0:08:29.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why had the bag sitting on the seat beside him been packed with a large quantity of snow?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.86,0:08:35.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's because he was imitating the legend of the Yuki-onna that's told in these mountains.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.53,0:08:38.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's stupid. I've known that guy since he was a kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.12,0:08:42.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He never gave a hoot about ghost stories.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.54,0:08:46.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And, even assuming that was true, I can't understand the reason for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.71,0:08:47.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who knows?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.34,0:08:53.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since we don't know how to ask a dead man, here's what I say...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.63,0:08:59.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it was murder, it would be one no human could possibly have done, an impossible crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.35,0:09:05.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yet, if we assume it could be done, naturally it could only have been the beautiful demon of the snowy mountain, the Yuki-onna.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.69,0:09:06.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you dumb or what?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.69,0:09:13.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's called a crime because a human being did it! And what's more, how could it be impossible! Idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.20,0:09:19.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Someone said that earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.16,0:09:23.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A boy came and objected to this story saying the same things that you just did.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.00,0:09:26.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was a middle-school student around the same age as you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.92,0:09:28.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A-A middle-schooler?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.46,0:09:29.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H-Heiji
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.68,0:09:45.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Exactly. You made such a big scene in the cafeteria, someone must be making fun of you and laughing.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.10,0:09:50.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Idiot! That was because you were frightened by that Yuki-onna talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.44,0:09:53.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I just thought I'd wake up your sleepy-thinking head.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.23,0:09:59.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wasn't frightened! I just thought it sounded real.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.36,0:10:03.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yuki-onna stories... There are a lot of them that are sad and feel real.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.99,0:10:07.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, it definitely sounded mysterious.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.75,0:10:16.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In Japan's most famous Yuki-onna story, the monster is called "Woman of the Snow." Isn't that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.92,0:10:20.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,English? Doesn't the Yuki-onna come from a Japanese story?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.72,0:10:22.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, it's from Japanese folklore.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.22,0:10:32.94,Signs,,0,0,0,,Translator's Note: Lafcadio Hearn was a writer and journalist who moved to Japan in 1890 and wrote a number of works including {\i1}Kwaidan: Stories and Studies of Strange Things{\i0}, in which the story in question is included.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.22,0:10:27.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That story was written in Japan by an English teacher; Lafcadio Hearn he was called.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.43,0:10:32.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was published in English. You've heard of Koizumi Yakumo? That was his pen name.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.19,0:10:37.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, yes. Shin'ichi is so clever that he knows everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.94,0:10:42.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, thank you. You said those things so I wouldn't be frightened, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.99,0:10:47.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even though I didn't say it, I had a bad feeling.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.29,0:10:52.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A premonition that this might turn into a storm.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.88,0:11:04.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait, Heiji. What would you do if a real Yuki-onna appeared?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.51,0:11:08.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Idiot, if there were such a woman, I'd like to meet her.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.68,0:11:09.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Heiji!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.23,0:11:14.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To solve this four-year old case, first I have to examine the lift in question.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.94,0:11:17.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And I need to get ahead of that other middle-schooler.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.07,0:11:23.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You don't need to worry about that It just means there's another person who thinks the same as you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.82,0:11:29.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why I can't lose! If he beats me, people will think I'm at a middle-schooler's level too.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.58,0:11:31.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You are a middle-schooler.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.50,0:11:33.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's the couple in love!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.25,0:11:36.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Idiot, it's not like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.88,0:11:40.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They say when two people trace out their love with their ski tracks, the snow will melt!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.17,0:11:43.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see, she's talking about those other people.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.64,0:11:48.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, if you're going to check out the lift, you'll have to come back later when this snowstorm's settled down.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.14,0:11:51.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's OK, but first...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.40,0:11:54.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.06,0:11:56.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, no, it was my fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.11,0:12:00.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Heiji?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.86,0:12:03.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey! Knock it off already!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.49,0:12:05.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You've been watching us and filming for quite a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.53,0:12:09.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Heiji, it's OK! She's probably just filming the snow-covered scenery.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.58,0:12:14.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, no. This old lady's been filming me!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.88,0:12:16.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because she's my mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.46,0:12:25.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's my Heiji. You're perceptive instincts are just like Heizou's.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.51,0:12:27.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, what are you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.14,0:12:32.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Heiji's almost never been to the north-east before, so I was worried!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.64,0:12:38.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't be silly! She's just adding to the video collection she's making of me from when I was born all the way until I'm an adult
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.94,0:12:40.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think I want to see that.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.44,0:12:43.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There was a snowstorm just like this then too.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.28,0:12:48.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On that day four years ago when Mizugami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} committed suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.16,0:12:51.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,t feels like that day too. Were we're also waiting until we could film.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.75,0:12:54.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And Minowa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} was surrounded by fans then also.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.00,0:12:58.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Looks like the snowstorm is starting to settle down.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.63,0:13:00.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.92,0:13:03.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, will you let us see you ski?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.17,0:13:07.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Show us you're skiing techniques from Yuki-onna's Love and Mystery.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.64,0:13:08.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.01,0:13:12.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That'll be difficult We'll be starting to film now.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.77,0:13:13.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.39,0:13:18.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since we got here, you fans have demanded he ski for you three times already.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.69,0:13:22.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you want to see him skiing, go and watch the movies!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.86,0:13:24.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What should I do?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.32,0:13:28.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wei I, the schedule is tight, but we have to make sacrifices for our important fans.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.66,0:13:32.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wouldn't Mizugami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-senpai{\r} have said it this way?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.29,0:13:34.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It will work out somehow.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.83,0:13:38.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Geez, he's no longer here, so forget that stuff!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.75,0:13:46.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry. Here you and Mizugami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} were going to become man and wife, and we have you involved in this movie about his death.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.76,0:13:53.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, I was the one who asked to participate. One way or another I feel there's something I need to know.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.60,0:13:56.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Some truth about his death might come out when we film this movie.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.02,0:14:04.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Two places then...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.03,0:14:04.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.32,0:14:10.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can see it from below. There are two places where the lift gets close to the slope.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.62,0:14:13.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, could somebody have jumped on?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.54,0:14:16.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, it gets close, but it's still three meters difference.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.16,0:14:19.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It'd be impossible without a trampoline.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.38,0:14:26.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that the Minowa Shouhei guy we saw at the hotel?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.17,0:14:28.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's pretty good.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.81,0:14:47.40,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Encore! Encore! Encore! Encore! Encore!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.69,0:14:45.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way, that was the one time for today.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.94,0:14:47.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For the next one, please watch the movie.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.03,0:14:53.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's already close to four. We need to hurry and shoot the scene at the top of the slope.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.41,0:14:58.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then why don't you ride the lift up before me. It'll be pitch black after five.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.79,0:14:59.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Director.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.50,0:15:04.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Have you seen hide or hair of the make-up specialist girl or the stuntman?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.96,0:15:08.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, those two said they were starting up on the lift before us.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.51,0:15:12.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's something...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.26,0:15:15.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's definitely something about this lift.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.64,0:15:18.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H-Hey, Heiji. Doesn't this lift scare you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.06,0:15:23.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's that, Kazuha? Since you're in the advanced class, you've been on lifts before, haven't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.65,0:15:27.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I have, but they were a different type than this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.61,0:15:32.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh no, it starting to blow up again.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.24,0:15:36.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can't even see the outline of the detective guy that's riding ahead of us anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.87,0:15:38.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Tateishi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.83,0:15:40.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, Mimata{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.54,0:15:43.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you doing on the down lift?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.58,0:15:45.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I kinda missed my chance to get off.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.92,0:15:47.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm not very good with things like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.89,0:15:57.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shin'ichi!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.89,0:16:00.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-What was that noise?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.10,0:16:03.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The sound of a pistol. That's what the sound was.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.73,0:16:04.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The director, Ooyama.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.36,0:16:06.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The actor, Minowa.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.40,0:16:09.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then the detective guy. That was the order.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.74,0:16:12.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,D-Did something happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.95,0:16:14.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, it's you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.07,0:16:18.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, I don't know. I was just getting off now too.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.51,0:16:37.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Stop the lift!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.89,0:16:40.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Take a look and figure it out! At that!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.68,0:16:45.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just stop the lift right away! Then call the police and paramedics!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.85,0:16:47.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is it, Shin'ichi? Did something happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.15,0:16:49.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran, don't look!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.57,0:16:55.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The lift's stopped.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.53,0:16:59.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's going on? First that "bang" noise, now a scream.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.91,0:17:06.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The lift, a gunshot Could it be that the same thing that happened four years ago is happening now?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.04,0:17:13.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We are extremely sorry for any inconvenience to our guests. Please wait a short while until lift operations are restored.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.72,0:17:15.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What does that mean? It's like that day.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.01,0:17:17.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.72,0:17:21.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When Mizugami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-senpai{\r} shot himself. That day.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.10,0:17:23.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mizugami...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.23,0:17:28.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The muzzle of the gun was pressed into his temple. Bang! It's suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.27,0:17:31.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. He was holding the gun in his right hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.52,0:17:34.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The problem is this bag next to the dead man.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.36,0:17:38.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I have an unpleasant feeling that I know what's inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.99,0:17:40.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like I thought, it's snow.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.16,0:17:43.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Geez, it's just like four years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.21,0:17:49.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think I remember hearing that you were going to film a movie here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.67,0:17:50.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.79,0:17:54.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A movie relating the incident four years ago to the legend.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.59,0:17:57.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But now our lead actor, Minowa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, has ended up like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.68,0:17:59.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eh, Minowa? The actor?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.80,0:18:02.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I'm not mistaken, you were there at the time of the incident four years ago as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.10,0:18:07.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm the movie's director, Ooyama. I was riding the lift directly in front of his.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.85,0:18:12.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When I heard the gunshot, I was just getting off the lift
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.19,0:18:14.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That boy was the one who noticed what happened to Minowa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.53,0:18:18.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, kid! What do you think you're doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.49,0:18:21.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Excuse me, if we don't start the lift soon, what will we do about the customers?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.66,0:18:25.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,OK, once we get the body and check for any related articles, you can start it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.58,0:18:27.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Need a hand?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.79,0:18:29.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, it's relatively light.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.96,0:18:33.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's slimmer than he looks, no more than 60 kilograms (132lbs).
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.13,0:18:36.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He wouldn't appear in anything except winter dramas and movies.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.30,0:18:40.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He said he didn't want people to see his underweight body.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.14,0:18:47.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why did he have his skis behind him instead of wearing them?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.18,0:18:51.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well now, that's probably because he had to carry this bag stuffed with snow.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.86,0:18:56.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Although it's full of snow now, it's big enough for a child to fit in.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.11,0:18:59.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,OK, go ahead and start the lift.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.99,0:19:01.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, Mr. Policeman!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.78,0:19:04.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There are three points I'm concerned about.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.04,0:19:09.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, it's finally moving.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.42,0:19:14.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There are a lot of people gathered there. I'm afraid.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.67,0:19:17.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Idiot! It's making me all excited!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.67,0:19:20.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Outsiders stay back! Stay back!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.59,0:19:22.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What? What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.72,0:19:23.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, it's you, kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.68,0:19:29.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Roughly, according to what they said, it looks like it's the same as the case four years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.85,0:19:36.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems a man riding by himself on the lift, with a bag full of snow beside him, shot himself with a gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.15,0:19:39.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As if he'd been possessed by the Yuki-onna.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.03,0:19:41.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Geez, you again.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.86,0:19:43.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This isn't your jurisdiction!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.20,0:19:47.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nope, I've quit being a police detective. I'm private now.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.16,0:19:52.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And what's more, I was riding on the lift directly behind the victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.37,0:19:55.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't you have some things to ask me, Mr. Detective?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.54,0:19:58.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Victim?" He committed suicide!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.21,0:20:00.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, it's too early to decide that
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.59,0:20:03.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H-Hey, Heiji! Save me!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.38,0:20:05.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you doing? Hurry and get off!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.93,0:20:07.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How? I don't know how to get off!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.93,0:20:12.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that case, when you reach the bottom the lift will stop again. Be sure to get off then.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.27,0:20:13.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,OK. OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.81,0:20:17.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That idiot, that's why I told her not to come.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.32,0:20:20.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come to think of it, there was another customer who didn't get off earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.57,0:20:21.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that true?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.53,0:20:26.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it was a pretty woman who had her hair tied in the back.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.28,0:20:31.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Noway! Minowa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} killed himself? Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.58,0:20:34.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Before we wonder why, could you answer a few questions for me?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.08,0:20:38.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like why you didn't get off the lift here before.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.29,0:20:41.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I couldn't get off! I'm not good with these things.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.63,0:20:47.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that kinda strange? Shouldn't you have come here four years ago to film that movie?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.30,0:20:51.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That time Mizugami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} rode up with me. This time I came with Mimata{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.89,0:20:53.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She's not very athletic.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.81,0:20:58.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? Didn't I hear from the director that you went up earlier?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.90,0:21:01.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How is it you were riding the lift with her?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.61,0:21:09.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The film crew was standing by but the director and lead actor hadn't come up yet So I skied down to call them.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.66,0:21:15.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On the way I noticed her riding down on the lift, and when I called to her, the gunshot went off.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.08,0:21:22.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I had a strange premonition about it, and so I asked Mimata{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} to ride up on the lift with me, and that's how we came up here.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.84,0:21:24.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because of what happened four years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.17,0:21:28.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then the lift stopped, and we were just now able to get off.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.97,0:21:34.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see. In other words, the director, Ooyama, who rode the lift in front of Minowa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.64,0:21:37.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the detective, Katashina{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who rode behind,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.90,0:21:41.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tateishi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who was on the down lift as it passed by,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.15,0:21:43.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and Mimata{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who was on the slope.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.44,0:21:47.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All of you were able to shoot Minowa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.82,0:21:48.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H-Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.99,0:21:55.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, now! Didn't you hear what I said just now? When the gunshot went off, I was with Mimata{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.16,0:22:01.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If that gunshot was a fake, then the crime becomes possible. That's what you were going to say, right, kid?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.25,0:22:03.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's it exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.42,0:22:06.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But don't you remember that Minowa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} was holding onto the gun?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.76,0:22:09.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How could something like that be done from a distance?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.39,0:22:14.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You aren't going to say we held onto the murder weapon after shooting him are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.35,0:22:17.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Furthermore, at the time the snow was blowing pretty violently.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.52,0:22:20.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wouldn't you think it'd be impossible to shoot him without a considerable degree of skill?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.61,0:22:24.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, I haven't considered all that yet, but there are some things that are suspicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.15,0:22:28.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,First of all, the ski poles from the lift Minowa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was riding.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.78,0:22:33.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The circular fittings attached to the ends have been inverted on both poles.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.79,0:22:36.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's proof they were used for something.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.79,0:22:40.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The next one is the lift Minowa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was riding.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.50,0:22:44.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In the plastic on the left side of the seat, there's a place where it's been cracked.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.38,0:22:48.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That could also have been used for some kind of trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.17,0:22:54.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the last one is the cloth bag that Minowa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} had riding beside him, stuffed with snow.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.64,0:22:57.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't why, but it's frozen solid.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.93,0:23:00.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Stop that You mustn't touch the evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.40,0:23:04.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I must say everywhere I go nowadays there are middle-school students brimming with curiosity.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.65,0:23:12.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There was one earlier. A middle-school student who was arrogantly pointing out the exact same three points to us policemen as you did.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.78,0:23:14.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What did you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.08,0:23:16.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was here just before you came.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.58,0:23:22.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm finally off. I'm never riding that lift again.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.21,0:23:24.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kazuha!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.04,0:23:26.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Aren't you in the advanced ski class?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.51,0:23:29.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And you don't know how to get off a lift?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.47,0:23:30.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Confess!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.13,0:23:34.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You wanted to be in the same advanced class with Hattori, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.43,0:23:36.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So your sprained leg is fake too...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.76,0:23:38.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah! That's not true!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.68,0:23:41.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's OK, we'll keep it a secret from Hattori.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.60,0:23:46.27,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Excuse me! Is there anyone here who happened to videotape Minowa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} earlier when he was getting on the lift?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.98,0:23:43.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm really sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.27,0:23:48.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're welcome to my video.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.36,0:23:51.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.36,0:23:54.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My, this is really well filmed.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.49,0:23:57.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I would have expected Minowa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s fans to only follow him.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.79,0:24:04.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, my son asked me to do that He told me to film the lift boarding platform as a reference for the incident four years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.58,0:24:06.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is your son a police detective or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.75,0:24:11.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's just a regular middle-school student It seems he wants to be a detective though.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.59,0:24:14.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Detective, eh? It's the same with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.01,0:24:18.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's this? Shin{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r} is busy chatting with some beautiful madame.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.47,0:24:20.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Geez, he sure takes after someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.89,0:24:25.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nope, that face is his detective face. He's still a greenie.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.06,0:24:31.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, can the self-styled world's preeminent mystery writer solve this case?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.90,0:24:34.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yukiko, that's a silly question.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.49,0:24:36.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eh? Yu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r} already figured it out?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.16,0:24:41.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I just came here to get hints about the incident four years ago for a book I'm writing.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.29,0:24:47.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But it's already too late, what with that movie their filming. And then virtually the same incident occurs a second time...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.92,0:24:50.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, if you know who the criminal is, rush over and tell the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.09,0:24:55.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nope, I'm going to entrust this to the youngsters and sit back and watch what develops.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.13,0:24:57.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But won't you give me a little hint?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.18,0:25:04.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you know? There's another legend in these mountains about the Yuki-onna.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.77,0:25:08.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A painful and sad tale...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.74,0:25:15.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What? The actor, Minowa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, committed suicide?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.24,0:25:17.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you sure, Heiji!?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.03,0:25:19.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't use such a loud voice!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.45,0:25:20.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is still off-the-record.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.12,0:25:23.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why do I have to be quiet?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.08,0:25:25.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wei I, I'm still not sure what happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.12,0:25:27.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For a suicide, it was suspicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.00,0:25:29.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's just like a case from four years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.54,0:25:32.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But it really was suicide, wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.26,0:25:35.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's exactly why I need to see the video.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.09,0:25:38.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well? Did you figure something out, Heiji?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.22,0:25:40.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just as I thought...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.01,0:25:42.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was definitely murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.60,0:25:46.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You know, I didn't expect this video to be so popular.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.89,0:25:48.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Popular?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.06,0:25:52.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There were some other people besides you who asked to see this video.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:53.11,0:25:55.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me it was a middle-schooler!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.28,0:25:57.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, one of them was.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.74,0:25:59.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One of them? You mean there were others?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.53,0:26:04.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A long while before that boy, there was a dandily dressed man with a mustache.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.87,0:26:06.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A man with a mustache?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.92,0:26:10.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Another Yuki-onna legend?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.54,0:26:12.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is there a hint about this case in it?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.92,0:26:16.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Listen to the whole story before you ask questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.80,0:26:19.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A long time ago, on a snowy evening...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.93,0:26:24.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Descending from the mountain and hurrying along the road home was a man by the name of Mokichi.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.39,0:26:32.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Along the road, he came across a very beautiful woman with long hair dressed in a silver gown.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.15,0:26:36.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The woman gave him a friendly look and said:
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.70,0:26:40.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've injured my leg on the mountain.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.45,0:26:42.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can no longer manage even a single step.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.78,0:26:46.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Would you please carry me to my home?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.58,0:26:54.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When Mokichi inquired where her home was, without speaking she pointed at the dark black forest where no road ran.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:54.88,0:27:00.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, the farther and farther they went, the deeper the snow became, and they never came within sight of the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.84,0:27:03.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Yamato man earnestly inquired:
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.72,0:27:06.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Have I perhaps lost the way?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.81,0:27:09.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The woman nodded silently.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.44,0:27:11.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She had been waiting...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:11.44,0:27:13.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For the man to abandon her.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.52,0:27:15.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.86,0:27:23.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The woman's true character was one who waits until a man's strength falters, and then consumes his soul: a Yuki-onna.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.41,0:27:31.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Before long the man's progress started to slow, and after a long silence, his lips began to move:
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.75,0:27:33.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Miss...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.46,0:27:37.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The woman had been waiting and hoping for this, and with a smile she replied:
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.05,0:27:40.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes? What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.68,0:27:45.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Out of breath, in a strained voice Mokichi said:
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.47,0:27:46.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Aren't you cold?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.35,0:27:53.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The man's unexpected question surprised the Yuki-onna and left her at a loss for words.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.69,0:27:59.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mokichi was numb from the cold, and afraid for his life, but nevertheless he continued:
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.11,0:28:01.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's uncomfortable in that basket, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.24,0:28:03.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Aren't you hungry?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.28,0:28:08.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just a little more patience. Hold on. Just hold on!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.95,0:28:11.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The woman's only reply was "yes".
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.00,0:28:17.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Her voice gradually grew weaker, until at last he could no longer hear her.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.21,0:28:19.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Concerned, he stopped walking...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.17,0:28:23.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And when he peered into the basket...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.76,0:28:25.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The woman had disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.76,0:28:31.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In her place there was only a large quantity of snow wrapped inside her silver gown.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.10,0:28:33.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.27,0:28:38.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The warmth of Mokichi's heart melted the Yuki-onna's cold one, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.23,0:28:39.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.28,0:28:40.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.11,0:28:41.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where was the hint in that?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.61,0:28:44.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hmm. As I feared, the load was too heavy for you, wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.11,0:28:48.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But for him, it might make a good practice exercise.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.53,0:28:49.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Him?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.49,0:28:56.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perhaps he's watching Minowa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s movies at the hotel now, if he really is my son.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.79,0:28:59.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look! Just as I thought!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.00,0:29:03.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Didn't you think Minowa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s skiing in this video is a little different from what we saw today?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.51,0:29:06.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Really? I think they're both great
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.34,0:29:08.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's a well known professional after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.39,0:29:10.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, look!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.68,0:29:13.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This part, where Minowa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} is rescuing the heroine that fainted.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.64,0:29:18.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When he's skiing down, until he goes out of frame, his cap strap... Look, it's attached.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.81,0:29:23.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But when he comes into the frame again, when he rushes over to her, it's no longer attached.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.40,0:29:25.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even though they're both in the same cut
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.28,0:29:26.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's true...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.24,0:29:27.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could it be a double?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.99,0:29:29.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe he can't really ski.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.70,0:29:34.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That can't be it! Earlier he was really ripping! It was cool!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.46,0:29:36.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you sure it was him?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.25,0:29:37.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course I am!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.96,0:29:39.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I have it on video.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.84,0:29:43.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See, told you.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.17,0:29:44.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, Sonoko...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.63,0:29:48.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you know where Minowa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} left his bag while he was skiing?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.47,0:29:52.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, he left it in front of his fans.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.14,0:29:56.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He said there was something important in it and asked us to watch it until he returned.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.06,0:29:57.65,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Souvenir Counter
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.35,0:29:57.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What? This bag?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.06,0:29:59.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A middle-schooler came to look at it?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.02,0:30:00.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When was this?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.32,0:30:04.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just a bit ago. He didn't buy one though.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.82,0:30:09.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, if that's too small for your needs, we have a larger size with the same design.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.32,0:30:10.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, no thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.95,0:30:13.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This belt can be lengthened like this; that can be very convenient.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.08,0:30:15.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, it really is!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.20,0:30:16.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How's that convenient?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.91,0:30:19.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey Heiji, what are you so angry about?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.04,0:30:20.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why shouldn't I be?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.46,0:30:23.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No matter where I go, that middle-schooler is one step ahead of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.34,0:30:26.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He rented the video from the hotel before me.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:27.26,0:30:29.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then there's that weird guy with the mustache.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.80,0:30:32.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If this keeps up, they'll solve the case before me.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.81,0:30:35.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You mean you haven't figured anything out yet, Heiji?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.56,0:30:40.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, I already knew who the murderer was and how they did it when we were back in the shop.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.06,0:30:43.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If that case, shouldn't you go to the police right away?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.61,0:30:45.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But it's not completely solved!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.44,0:30:50.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like the inverted ring on the ski poles and the frozen bag full of snow...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.20,0:30:54.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I can't figure those out, then my reasoning won't be complete.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.37,0:30:59.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is it, Shizu? Didn't I tell you not to make personal calls to me while I'm working?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.58,0:31:01.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What? A case you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.04,0:31:03.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Found it!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.00,0:31:04.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is it!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.67,0:31:05.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:05.71,0:31:10.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Remember? Didn't we hear a sound just before the deceased Minowa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} reached the top of the lift?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.55,0:31:12.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A sound like a gunshot?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.55,0:31:15.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since they haven't retrieved this yet...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.64,0:31:18.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The criminal must still be somewhere they can't get away from.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.93,0:31:22.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, sounds like you know everything already.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.94,0:31:27.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, the crucial trick used to commit the murder still hasn't come to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.61,0:31:30.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The crack left on the lift to the left side of the corpse...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.28,0:31:31.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What caused that?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.99,0:31:36.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And that bag of snow. Even though I know who the criminal is, I don't see how that's connected.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.66,0:31:38.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eh? You know who the criminal is?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.66,0:31:42.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it's one of the four suspects the police are questioning now.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.79,0:31:45.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The one who was riding the lift just before Minowa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}: Ooyama, the director...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.42,0:31:49.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The one riding just behind Minowa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}: the detective, Katashina{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.17,0:31:53.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The one on the slopes going to call the director and the others: the stuntman, Mimata{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.18,0:31:56.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the one who missed getting off the lift: Tateishi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.10,0:32:03.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait a second, other than the director, Ooyama, how do you know which order the other three boarded in?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.27,0:32:06.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's because I told him.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.32,0:32:07.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,S-Shin'ichi's mother?!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.44,0:32:13.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I just happened to be in the right place to overhear when they were talking with the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.32,0:32:16.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Really? But how... why?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.24,0:32:17.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a complete coincidence!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.62,0:32:21.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My husband's and my vacation just happened to coincide with Shin{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}'s ski lessons.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.16,0:32:22.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just happened to coincide, eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.12,0:32:24.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But Shin{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.71,0:32:26.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're thirty minutes late.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.25,0:32:31.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was just here. Another middle-school boy just like Shin{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.80,0:32:39.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What? You mean there's another middle-school detective idiot like Shin'ichi here? How weird!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.06,0:32:43.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Speaking of another, did you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.48,0:32:46.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's another legend about the Yuki-onna and her silver robe.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.23,0:32:49.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Damn, it's already pitch black.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.65,0:32:55.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even though the criminal's been held this long for police questioning, when they release them, they'll be able to hide the evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.61,0:32:56.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Heiji!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.82,0:32:58.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.45,0:33:00.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Using the rain will form a puddle.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.08,0:33:02.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With snow, you can make a snowman.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.08,0:33:07.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But if it's ice, you can use it to make an enormous statue.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.21,0:33:12.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yusaku said it was the key to solving the mystery of this case.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.26,0:33:16.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't be led astray by the way things appear, Heiji. By Heizou.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.84,0:33:18.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.01,0:33:21.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What does that snowman story have to do...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.47,0:33:23.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H-Heiji?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.73,0:33:33.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Can we get this over with?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.24,0:33:38.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry, but could you get the phone from my coat pocket?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.41,0:33:40.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who's there?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.78,0:33:42.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We're a little busy right now...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.62,0:33:44.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I understand it all now.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.58,0:33:50.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I know who murdered Minowa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and made it appear to be a suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:50.92,0:33:53.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the trick the murderer used to make it possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.84,0:33:54.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I know it all.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.09,0:33:58.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Geez, that middle-school kid again.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.26,0:34:03.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So are you here to tell us again that how the four of us could have killed Minowa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.39,0:34:05.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We already told you, it was impossible for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:06.39,0:34:10.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was by himself on the lift, so we couldn't have placed the gun in his hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:10.19,0:34:14.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Besides, except for the detective who's a former policeman,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:14.32,0:34:17.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We wouldn't have been able to aim at and shoot him in the head during that snowstorm.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.07,0:34:19.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:19.70,0:34:21.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That'd be impossible for a former policeman also.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.66,0:34:25.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At any rate, in that snowstorm I could barely see his lift in front of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.87,0:34:27.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's exactly it.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.29,0:34:29.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The murder would have been impossible in that situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.38,0:34:32.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If Minowa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} really was...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.17,0:34:35.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Really riding alone on the lift.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:38.22,0:34:38.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What did you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.47,0:34:40.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, now...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.47,0:34:44.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're not saying there was someone riding along inside the bag are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.60,0:34:49.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But that bag was packed with snow, and an adult would be way too big to fit inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.98,0:34:53.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, no. They hid in this bigger bag.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.65,0:34:59.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They sell a larger sized version with the same design as the bag that was packed with snow at the shop in the hotel.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.53,0:35:00.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's crazy.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.70,0:35:06.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you saying Minowa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} intentionally carried a bag with the criminal in it and got on the lift with it?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.20,0:35:12.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, the person in the bag wasn't the criminal, but Minowa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.42,0:35:14.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Noway! How can that be?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.38,0:35:16.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then the one carrying the bag...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.46,0:35:17.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was the criminal.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.09,0:35:23.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Minowa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s face was mostly hidden by his hair, and he was wearing sunglasses at the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.39,0:35:28.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If he was wearing a wig, a knit hat, sunglasses, and ski-wear...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.68,0:35:31.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It could easily seem like it was him.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.56,0:35:35.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But didn't he have a conversation with our fans?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.98,0:35:38.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They'd have no problem hearing Minowa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s voice.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.82,0:35:40.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But how?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.03,0:35:46.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The real Minowa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} listened carefully from within the bag and replied appropriately.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:46.74,0:35:51.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That way it wouldn't be that much of a stretch to believe the disguised criminal was Minowa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, would it?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.00,0:35:53.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,N-No way...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.50,0:35:54.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.67,0:35:57.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why he didn't say anything at the time until he picked up the bag.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.34,0:36:00.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You must be joking.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.01,0:36:04.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With his excessive pride, he'd never hide inside a bag.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.18,0:36:06.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's probably...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.43,0:36:09.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Exactly why he hid, because of his pride.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:09.85,0:36:12.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Likely his professional level skiing skills...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.10,0:36:17.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Were just a facade, made up for appearances. They were nothing but a lie.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.86,0:36:19.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A lie?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.23,0:36:23.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, he may have been able to ski a bit, but I don't think he was at a professional level.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.91,0:36:31.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I watched Minowa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s ski-scenes in the movies {\i1}Yuki-onna's Love{\i0} and {\i1}Yuki-onna's Mystery{\i0} at the hotel.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.50,0:36:38.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And in the scenes where he was skiing over to the heroine, he always intentionally went out of the frame and then came back in.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.09,0:36:44.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's more, when he was skiing the strap on his cap was attached, but in the close-ups, it wasn't
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.64,0:36:47.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, the skiing must have been done by someone else.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.72,0:36:50.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that right, Mr. Director?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.93,0:36:51.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.18,0:36:57.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It wasn't because he couldn't ski, but he had injured his leg during the first movie.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.90,0:37:04.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nevertheless, he still insisted on doing the skiing himself, so in order to convince him we secretly put in a double.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.32,0:37:09.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ironically, those ski scenes were praised by the critics.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.53,0:37:12.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In the second movie we used a double again so no one would notice.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.79,0:37:14.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You did?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:14.25,0:37:21.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And so, when the fans demanded it, he asked the double to ski for him and got inside the bag and waited at the bottom.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:21.59,0:37:27.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When the double came to pick-up the bag, he could appear to be holding up his end of the conversation with the fans.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:29.14,0:37:30.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, wait a second...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:30.51,0:37:33.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you saying the double was...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.73,0:37:40.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The one who Minowa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} asked to take on his role and carry him around in a bag, and used that to kill him was...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:43.65,0:37:45.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The stuntman, Mimata{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:46.57,0:37:48.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It can only have been you.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.82,0:37:50.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mimata{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:50.16,0:37:51.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that true?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.70,0:37:58.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I think the double used in the movies was the one who died four years ago, the stuntman Mizugami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.58,0:38:01.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The skiing in the movies was different from the skiing I saw today.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.75,0:38:07.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,More than likely before Mizugami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} died, he passed on the secret of the substitution to Mimata{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.30,0:38:11.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And he cleverly used it on this occasion to commit the crime on the lift.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.39,0:38:12.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Exactly...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.60,0:38:18.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,While on the lift, he pulled Minowa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s head from the bag, held it down, and shot a bullet through it.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:20.19,0:38:27.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He then pulled Minowa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} out of the bag, put the gun in his hand, and jumped off holding the bag.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:28.36,0:38:34.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On this lift there are two places where the height above the ground is around three meters.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.87,0:38:39.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So the hole in the seat was made when Minowa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was shot.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:39.96,0:38:43.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And when Minowa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} got onto the lift, he was sitting on the left side.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.92,0:38:49.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But when the body was found it was sitting on the right That's proof a crime occurred.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.72,0:38:54.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It would be difficult for a dead person to have switch seats on the lift, wouldn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:54.81,0:38:58.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But Mimata{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} was talking with me when we heard the gunshot.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.77,0:39:00.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was probably the sound of a bottle rocket.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.10,0:39:05.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After he jumped from the lift and put on the ski-wear he'd prepared,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.36,0:39:11.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He used the flame from a cigarette to light the fuse and placed it in a plastic bottle so it would launch later.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:11.95,0:39:18.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By skiing to the bottom and talking with someone when they heard the sound, he could provide a witness for his alibi.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.25,0:39:21.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But where did the bag filled with snow come from?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.54,0:39:22.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Didn't I just say?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.67,0:39:27.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There are two places on that lift where it's only three meters to the ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.09,0:39:32.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He could place a bag there, and then invert the ring on a ski pole and use it to hook onto it and pull it into the lift
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.47,0:39:33.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.43,0:39:34.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Three meters to the ground...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:35.14,0:39:42.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A ski pole is approximately 1 meter and 20 centimeters long. If you hook one strap onto the other to get more length, it might reach.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.19,0:39:45.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I wonder if you could use it to grab something during that snowstorm.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.27,0:39:47.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.40,0:39:50.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You use just one ski pole, and for the remaining meter...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.03,0:39:58.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You just have to lengthen the belt on the cloth bag, dampen it with water, freeze it, and it will provide the remaining meter.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.04,0:40:03.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The ring on the other pole was inverted so that the other one wouldn't be so noticeable.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:03.67,0:40:06.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But could he see the bag from the lift?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.88,0:40:09.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was blowing so badly you couldn't even see the lift in front of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.76,0:40:11.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.59,0:40:14.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The interval between the lifts is more than six seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.18,0:40:23.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The speed of the lift is around 1.5 to 2 meters per second, meaning the interval between the lifts is about 10 meters.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.85,0:40:28.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even if you can't see something ten meters ahead, you would be able to see a bag three meters below.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:29.15,0:40:32.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It would be even easier since he knew where the bag was.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.49,0:40:33.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, the evidence...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.99,0:40:35.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, there's evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.70,0:40:38.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since Mimata{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} met Tateishi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and went with her like that...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:39.33,0:40:44.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And was detained in this lodge for questioning, he should still be wearing it
Dialogue: 0,0:40:45.54,0:40:48.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Minowa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s matching ski-wear.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.96,0:40:53.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you happen to still have the bag Minowa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was hidden in?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:54.72,0:40:56.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've been enduring it this whole time.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:57.30,0:40:58.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And it's been pretty hot.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.26,0:41:00.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,M-Mimata{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:00.89,0:41:02.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So it was you after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:03.48,0:41:05.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You noticed it too, Director?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:05.31,0:41:05.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.48,0:41:09.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At first I thought he'd just got better at skiing.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:09.65,0:41:13.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When I saw his body, I realized it must have been you.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.99,0:41:15.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, why?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:15.99,0:41:20.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I did it to avenge the man who would have been your husband, Mizugami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-senpai{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:20.95,0:41:25.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Four years ago, Minowa used this same trick to kill him.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.71,0:41:27.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:27.50,0:41:34.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Remember, that day four years ago when Minowa was surrounded by demanding fans? Didn't he say it?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.63,0:41:41.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"It will work out somehow." He planned to transport Minowa secretly inside a bag.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:41.26,0:41:45.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But Minowa took advantage of his good will and killed him.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.27,0:41:48.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because he said he wanted to quit being a stuntman and become an actor.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.77,0:41:52.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When I shoved the gun in front of him, he finally admitted it.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.94,0:41:55.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That guy, how could I let him become an actor?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:56.03,0:41:58.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If we came into conflict, he'd expose me!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.99,0:42:01.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's what I scared out of him.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.08,0:42:07.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's ironic that the movie you were making matches this revenge plot.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.79,0:42:12.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The truth is I suspected Minowa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} was the criminal four years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:12.84,0:42:15.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why I decided to make this movie.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.63,0:42:21.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was a secret until now, but the criminal in the movie was the detective that Minowa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} was playing...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:21.39,0:42:25.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the trick was the same one Mimata{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} mentioned from four years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.56,0:42:30.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought he might give himself up when he saw the script.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:31.73,0:42:33.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even though I'm no longer a police detective...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.40,0:42:39.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wish if you knew that much, that you would have stopped this senseless murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:39.78,0:42:44.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Revenge just calls for more revenge, and the feeling of achievement fades quickly,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.87,0:42:47.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like a snowflake in the palm of your hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:53.63,0:42:56.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, well continue this down at the station.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.92,0:42:58.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Would you come along as well?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:59.13,0:43:00.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:00.30,0:43:02.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do I do about this other middle-school student on the phone?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:03.39,0:43:08.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His deduction was exactly the same as this kid's; he said everything over the phone at about the same time too.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:12.44,0:43:15.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Heiji, why didn't you go with the police?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:15.98,0:43:20.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Idiot, didn't I say someone would carry you down to the hotel? Fool.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.91,0:43:27.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I only solved the thing about freezing the belt on the bag because of Dad's hint.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:27.95,0:43:31.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That middle-schooler was able to solve it all by himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:31.29,0:43:32.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't want to meet him.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:33.25,0:43:34.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why not?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:34.63,0:43:41.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You just have to take the plastic bottle and say you solved the case, so shouldn't you go see them?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.01,0:43:48.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I had to hear the story from Dad about the Yuki-onna pretending her leg was injured and getting into the basket
Dialogue: 0,0:43:48.56,0:43:54.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Until then, I didn't realize Minowa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was just pretending to be good at skiing and got into the bag himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.65,0:43:56.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But you did all the deduction yourself, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:56.86,0:44:00.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, that other middle-schooler was the one who solved the case by himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:01.24,0:44:02.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It wasn't me.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:02.57,0:44:03.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:03.45,0:44:04.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Be quiet.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:04.66,0:44:07.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even with a sprain, you had to scamper around with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:07.41,0:44:11.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You wanted to show off by getting into the advanced ski class, but you overdid it while practicing and sprained your leg, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.75,0:44:17.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, thanks to you showing off, I knew that Minowa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was the one in the bag right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:18.09,0:44:21.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since you helped me out this time, I'll let it slide.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:21.76,0:44:22.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Idiot...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:22.84,0:44:27.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The reason I practiced so much wasn't to show off.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:28.85,0:44:32.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why are there two different Yuki-onna stories?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:33.06,0:44:35.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's because mothers tell them.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:37.02,0:44:42.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The original Yuki-onna legend was used to caution people not to go out during snowstorms.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:42.74,0:44:51.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When they tell the stories to their children, they sympathize with the Yuki-onna, and little by little they change the way they tell them.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:52.12,0:44:57.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why the original story where making the exchange for the silver gown leads to death
Dialogue: 0,0:44:57.21,0:45:01.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,changed into the story where she returns to the snow without taking his soul.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:02.26,0:45:06.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why there are a lot of Yuki-onna stories that are sad and seem real.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:14.48,0:45:16.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Although I couldn't see very well through the snow...
Dialogue: 0,0:45:16.73,0:45:17.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was him.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:18.15,0:45:19.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The other middle-schooler.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:19.73,0:45:22.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, even though we didn't meet, we're both detectives...
Dialogue: 0,0:45:22.65,0:45:25.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well meet again someday, upon the stage of mystery.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:56.04,0:47:01.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's how it was! And then that super smart detective left without even giving the police his name.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:02.13,0:47:05.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So? Isn't he a lot different than some other detective was before he was shrunk?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:05.96,0:47:08.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wasn't he was so cool and modest?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:09.76,0:47:12.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But that was me...
